# SPA history fallback for Render static sites.
#
# Without this, the host looks for a real file at /dashboard or /integrations and
# returns 404. That breaks page refreshes, shared links, and every OAuth return -
# the Gmail callback redirects to /integrations?gmail=connected, which 404s even
# though the connection succeeded.
#
# Status 200 makes it a REWRITE, not a redirect: the URL and query string are kept
# so React Router can read the path and params. A 301/302 would change the URL and
# throw away ?gmail=connected.
#
# Vite copies public/ into dist/ verbatim, so this ships with the build and needs no
# dashboard configuration. A same-origin deploy does not need it - Express handles
# the SPA fallback itself (see server/app.js).
/*    /index.html   200
